This paper deals with approximation algorithms for combinatorial optimization problems, specifically Max Bisection and Max 2-Sat. The techniques used involve graph partitioning and spectral methods, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of computer science related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), graph theory (cs.GT), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
